#Task 3: Machine Learning Model Development

# 1 Select a suitable machine learning task (classification, regression, or clustering) based on the nature of the dataset.
# 2 Split the dataset into training and testing sets.
# 3 Choose appropriate machine learning algorithms and models for the task.
# 4 Train the models using the training set and evaluate their performance using suitable evaluation metrics.
# 5 Compare the performance of different models and select the best-performing one.

# Train-test split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df.drop(columns=['Price']), df['Price'], test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

# Initialize and train the model
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Make predictions
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)

# Evaluate the model
mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
print("Mean Squared Error:", mse)
mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)
print("Mean Absolute MAE:", mae)
r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)
print('accuracy:',r2)

In [60]:
models = {
    'Logistic Regression': LogisticRegression(),
    'Decision Tree': DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    'Random Forest': RandomForestClassifier(),
    'SVM': SVC(),
    'KNN': KNeighborsClassifier(),
    'Gradient Boosting': GradientBoostingClassifier(),
    'AdaBoost': AdaBoostClassifier(), 
    'Naive Bayes': GaussianNB(),       
    'MLP Neural Network': MLPClassifier() 
}

for name, model in models.items():
    print(f"Training {name}...")
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    print(f"{name} Accuracy: {accuracy:.2f}")
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))

# Dictionary to store accuracies
accuracies = {}

for name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    accuracies[name] = accuracy

# Create a bar plot for accuracies
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.barh(list(accuracies.keys()), list(accuracies.values()), color='skyblue')

plt.title('Accuracy of Different Models')
plt.xlim(0, 1)
plt.gca().invert_yaxis() 
plt.show()
